http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Thu 29 Sep 2016
Source: OIE, WAHID weekly disease information 2016; 29(39) [edited]
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=21065


European foulbrood of honey bees, Norway
----------------------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 29 Sep 2016 from Dre Kristina Landsverk, Chief Veterinary Officer, Norwegian Food Safety Authority, Ministry of Agriculture and Food, Brumunddal, Norway

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 26 Sep 2016
Date of confirmation of the event: 26 Sep 2016
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 17 Jun 2016
Manifestation of disease: sub-clinical infection
Causal agent: _Melissococcus plutonius_
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks: Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1: Evje & Hornnes, Agder Department, South & West Region, Aust-Agder
Date of start of the outbreak: 26 Sep 2016
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: apiary
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Bees (hives) / 113 / 1 / - / - / -
Affected population: The hives are located at 6 different places.

Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Bees (hives) / 0.88 / ** / ** / **
* Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter
** Not calculated because of missing information

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive

Control measures
Measures applied: screening; quarantine; vaccination permitted (if a vaccine exists); no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: disinfection/disinfestations; stamping out

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Norwegian University of Life Sciences (NMBU) (national laboratory) / Bees / bacteriological examination / 26 Sep 2016 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Between 2012 to 2015, Norway reported 18 outbreaks of European foulbrood. The outbreaks were located in the counties of Hedmark, Aust-Agder (where the current outbreak is located) and Vestfold. The event was resolved on 17 Jun 2016. See event summary and updated map at http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review/viewsummary?reportid=12043. - Mod.CRD

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4526989,27903.]
